[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " when the day of Pentecost had come, they were all together in one place. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Suddenly"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a sound"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " like a violent wind blowing"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came from heaven"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and filled the entire house where they were sitting. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And tongues spreading out like a fire"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " appeared to them and came to rest on each one of them. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " All"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of them were filled with the Holy Spirit, and they began to speak in other languages"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as the Spirit enabled them."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now there were devout Jews"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from every nation under heaven residing in Jerusalem."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When this sound"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " occurred, a crowd gathered and was in confusion,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " because each one heard them speaking in his own language. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Completely baffled, they said,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Aren’t"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " all these who are speaking Galileans? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And how is it that each one of us hears them"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in our own native language?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Parthians, Medes, Elamites, and residents of Mesopotamia, Judea and Cappadocia, Pontus and the province of Asia,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Phrygia and Pamphylia, Egypt and the parts of Libya near Cyrene,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and visitors from Rome,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " both Jews and proselytes,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Cretans and Arabs – we hear them speaking in our own languages about the great deeds God has done!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " All were astounded and greatly confused, saying to one another, “What does this mean?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But others jeered at the speakers,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " saying, “They are drunk on new wine!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Peter stood up"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with the eleven, raised his voice, and addressed them: “You men of Judea"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and all you who live in Jerusalem,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " know this"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and listen carefully to what I say. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " In spite of what you think, these men are not drunk,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for it is only nine o’clock in the morning."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But this is what was spoken about through the prophet Joel:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "And"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the last days"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " it will be,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " God says,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "that I will pour out my Spirit on all people,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and your sons and your daughters will prophesy,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and your young men will see visions,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and your old men will dream dreams"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Even on my servants,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " both men and women,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "I will pour out my Spirit in those days, and they will prophesy"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "And I will perform wonders in the sky"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " above"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and miraculous signs"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " on the earth below,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "blood and fire and clouds of smoke"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "The sun will be changed to darkness"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and the moon to blood"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "before the great and glorious"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "day of the Lord comes"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "And then"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Men of Israel,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " listen to these words: Jesus the Nazarene, a man clearly attested to you by God with powerful deeds,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " wonders, and miraculous signs"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that God performed among you through him, just as you yourselves know – "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " this man, who was handed over by the predetermined plan and foreknowledge of God, you executed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by nailing him to a cross at the hands of Gentiles."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But God raised him up,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " having released"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " him from the pains"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of death, because it was not possible for him to be held in its power."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For David says about him,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "I saw the Lord always in front of me,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "for he is at my right hand so that I will not be shaken"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Therefore my heart was glad and my tongue rejoiced;"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "my body"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " also will live in hope,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "because you will not leave my soul in Hades,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "nor permit your Holy One to experience"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "decay"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "You have made known to me the paths of life;"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "you will make me full of joy with your presence"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Brothers,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I can speak confidently"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to you about our forefather"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " David, that he both died and was buried, and his tomb is with us to this day. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So then, because"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he was a prophet and knew that God "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "had sworn to him with an oath to seat one of his descendants"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "on his throne"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " David by foreseeing this"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " spoke about the resurrection of the Christ,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "he was neither abandoned to Hades"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " nor did his body"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " experience"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "decay"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " This Jesus God raised up, and we are all witnesses of it."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So then, exalted"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to the right hand"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of God, and having received"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the promise of the Holy Spirit"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from the Father, he has poured out"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " what you both see and hear. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For David did not ascend into heaven, but he himself says, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "The Lord said to my lord,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Sit"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " at my right hand "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "until I make your enemies a footstool"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "for your feet"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Therefore let all the house of Israel know beyond a doubt"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that God has made this Jesus whom you crucified"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " both Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and Christ.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now when they heard this,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they were acutely distressed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and said to Peter and the rest of the apostles, “What should we do, brothers?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Peter said to them, “Repent, and each one of you be baptized"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the name of Jesus Christ"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the forgiveness of your sins, and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For the promise"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is for you and your children, and for all who are far away, as many as the Lord our God will call to himself.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " With many other words he testified"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and exhorted them saying, “Save yourselves from this perverse"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " generation!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So those who accepted"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his message"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were baptized, and that day about three thousand people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were added."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They were devoting themselves to the apostles’ teaching and to fellowship,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to the breaking of bread and to prayer."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Reverential awe"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came over everyone,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and many wonders and miraculous signs"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came about by the apostles. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " All who believed were together and held"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " everything in common, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and they began selling"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " their property"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and possessions and distributing the proceeds"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to everyone, as anyone had need. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Every day"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they continued to gather together by common consent in the temple courts,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " breaking bread from"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " house to house, sharing their food with glad"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and humble hearts,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " praising God and having the good will"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of all the people. And the Lord was adding to their number every day"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " those who were being saved."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]